{"type":"message","id":"51cae3b4","parentId":"901ca89c","timestamp":"2026-03-24T15:04:55.734Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_varytcbpk6q2_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Pulse: 2026-03-24 110417\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\nRejected: research/CFI_COMPRESSION_EXPERIMENT.md (missing)\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state and determine what concrete action to take.\r\n\r\nFrom the goals:\r\n- Phase 0 and 1 are complete\r\n- CFI Analysis is done with key findings about frequency-invariants\r\n- Pending: CFI-weighted compression experiment (compare next-pulse prediction vs frequency baseline)\r\n\r\nThe last pulse noted \"No mutations applied this cycle\" - meaning the previous pulse didn't make any changes.\r\n\r\nKey insight: The next priority is the CFI-weighted compression experiment. This is about comparing CFI-based filtering vs frequency-based filtering for predicting next pulse content.\r\n\r\nLet me look at what files we have:\r\n- research/CFI_RESULTS.md - the analysis done\r\n- research/GAP-DECAY-MAPPING.md\r\n- research/ARCHITECTURE-COMPARISON.md\r\n\r\nThe experiment needs to:\r\n1. Take the invariants data from CFI analysis\r\n2. Compare two compression strategies:\r\n   - Frequency baseline: compress by highest frequency\r\n   - CFI-weighted: compress by highest CFI (causal strength)\r\n3. Test which better predicts next-pulse content\r\n\r\nI should design this experiment. The most concrete next step would be to create an experiment specification or script that can actually run this comparison.\r\n\r\nLet me create an experiment plan/design document that specifies how to run this comparison.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe CFI analysis revealed that only 5.7% of invariants have high CFI (>=0.7) and are true causal anchors, while 44.8% are pure noise. The next logical step is to test whether CFI-weighted compression outperforms frequency-based compression for predicting next-pulse content.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate an experiment specification for the CFI-weighted compression comparison, defining the test methodology and expected outputs.\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n`\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: # CFI-Weighted Compression Experiment\r\n\r\n## Hypothesis\r\nCFI-weighted compression will outperform frequency-based compression for predicting next-pulse content because it filters metaprogramming artifacts (CFI=0) that create noise in frequency analysis.\r\n\r\n## Methodology\r\n\r\n### Data Source\r\n- Source: `research/CFI_RESULTS.md` (44.8% CFI=0, 5.7% CFI>=0.7)\r\n- Test corpus: last 10 pulse files in `pulse_*.md`\r\n\r\n### Compression Strategies\r\n\r\n**Strategy A: Frequency Baseline**\r\n- Sort invariants by frequency (descending)\r\n- Take top N tokens\r\n- Calculate recall: how many tokens in next pulse are captured?\r\n\r\n**Strategy B: CFI-Weighted**\r\n- Sort invariants by CFI score (descending)\r\n- Take top N tokens\r\n- Calculate recall: how many tokens in next pulse are captured?\r\n\r\n### Metrics\r\n- **Recall@k**: % of next-pulse tokens captured in top-k compressed tokens\r\n- **Precision@k**: % of top-k compressed tokens that appear in next pulse\r\n- **CFI-Normalized Recall**: Weighted recall by CFI (true causal tokens count more)\r\n\r\n### Experiment Script (conceptual)\r\n```\r\nFor each pulse_i in corpus[1:]:\r\n  strategy_a_tokens = top_k_by_frequency(invariants, k=100)\r\n  strategy_b_tokens = top_k_by_cfi(invariants, k=100)\r\n  \r\n  next_pulse_tokens = tokens(pulse_{i+1})\r\n  \r\n  recall_a = overlap(strategy_a_tokens, next_pulse_tokens) / len(next_pulse_tokens)\r\n  recall_b = overlap(strategy_b_tokens, next_pulse_tokens) / len(next_pulse_tokens)\r\n```\r\n\r\n## Expected Outcome\r\n- Strategy B (CFI-weighted) should have higher recall for high-CFI tokens\r\n- Strategy A (frequency) may capture more format tokens (high freq, low CFI)\r\n- Net result: CFI-weighted better for research trajectory prediction\r\n\r\n## Next Steps\r\n- [ ] Extract invariant data into structured format\r\n- [ ] Implement comparison script\r\n- [ ] Run on last 10 pulses\r\n- [ ] Compare recall metrics\r\n- [ ] Update CFI_RESULTS.md with experiment results\r\n`\r\nfile: research/CFI_COMPRESSION_EXPERIMENT.md\r\n`\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 0\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 11:04:43\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774364695732}}
